	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I would imagine that a commented disassembly of a commercial game program done in a scholarly tone might fall under fair use as a comment on the program, as long as nobody tries to sell copies of a mod of that program. Compare to <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lions%27_Commentary_on_UNIX_6th_Edition,_with_Source_Code" class="postlink"><em>Lions' Commentary on UNIX</em></a>. But good luck getting the rom kiddies to produce such disassemblies.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


